cff-version: 1.2.0
title: DriftBench
message: "If you use DriftBench in your research, please cite it as below."
type: software
version: 1.0.0
date-released: "2026-05-30"
license: Apache-2.0
repository-code: "https://github.com/simon9679/driftbench"
abstract: >
  DriftBench is a deterministic benchmark for evaluating belief drift, conflict tracking,
  and identity transition in cognitive AI systems. It measures whether a system can track
  changing commitments, internal contradictions, and causally meaningful graph updates
  without relying on an LLM judge. All five metrics (CER, GCS, BDA, ISS, NRS) are
  fully reproducible: same input always produces the same scores.
keywords:
  - benchmark
  - cognitive AI
  - belief drift
  - AI evaluation
  - deterministic metrics
  - temporal belief graph
  - AI safety
  - language models
